item.description:
arXiv:2503.03482v1 Announce Type: new 
Abstract: We establish a new boundary version of spectral volume comparison theorem in this paper. Let $(M^n,g)(n\geq 3)$ be a connected, smooth compact n-dimensional manifold with weakly convex boundary. If there exist a positive function $w\in C^{\infty}(M)$ that satisfies: \begin{equation*}
  \begin{cases}
  -\frac{n-1}{n-2}\Delta w+\Ric w\geq (n-1)w,
  \frac{\partial w}{\partial \eta}=0.
  \end{cases} \end{equation*} then $\Vol(M)\leq \Vol(\bS^n_{+})$, and equality holds if and only if $M^n$ is isometric to the unit round hemisphere $\bS^{n}_{+}=\{x\in\bR^{n+1}: |x|=1, x_{n+1}\geq 0\}\subset\bR^{n+1}$.
